did the Depositor's Trust.

799
00:40:26,700 --> 00:40:28,133
We don't go off half-cocked.

800
00:40:28,167 --> 00:40:30,600
Who knows how deep it runs?

801
00:40:30,633 --> 00:40:33,133
Meaning you
checked me out first.

802
00:40:33,167 --> 00:40:34,300
Meaning I followed procedure

803
00:40:34,333 --> 00:40:36,000
and ran an official
profile on you.

804
00:40:36,033 --> 00:40:40,400
Sit down.

805
00:40:40,433 --> 00:40:43,367
Who said it was cops?

806
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:45,567
Nick Scarzi, local OC.

807
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:47,333
He's just testing the
waters with this tidbit

808
00:40:47,367 --> 00:40:48,900
and wants us to
pony up $500 grand

809
00:40:48,933 --> 00:40:50,700
before he'll tell us
what else he knows.

810
00:40:50,733 --> 00:40:53,000
Scarzi? First off,
he's not mob.

811
00:40:53,033 --> 00:40:55,167
He's an errand boy.

812
00:40:55,200 --> 00:40:57,567
A nightclub owner.
Strictly small time.

813
00:40:57,600 --> 00:41:00,300
You'd actually pay
him 500 large ones?

814
00:41:00,333 --> 00:41:01,833
Money's not an issue
if Scarzi's gonna give us

815
00:41:01,867 --> 00:41:03,600
the Depositor's Trust.

816
00:41:03,633 --> 00:41:05,467
Did Scarzi tell you
that Jimmy Donnelly,

817
00:41:05,500 --> 00:41:07,233
the walking man in
Medford that night,

818
00:41:07,267 --> 00:41:10,200
is pals
with a certain somebody?

819
00:41:10,233 --> 00:41:12,133
Like I told ya, Scarzi's
not gonna play ball with us

820
00:41:12,167 --> 00:41:13,867
until we do a deal with him.

821
00:41:13,900 --> 00:41:18,167
That certain somebody
I followed up elsewhere.

822
00:41:18,200 --> 00:41:19,967
Gerry Clemente.

823
00:41:20,067 --> 00:41:21,833
(phone rings)

824
00:41:21,867 --> 00:41:23,500
- Yeah?
- Gerry. Nick Scarzi.

825
00:41:23,533 --> 00:41:24,933
They're after me.

826
00:41:24,967 --> 00:41:27,200
- Who?
- The mob! That's who!

827
00:41:27,233 --> 00:41:28,533
What are you talkin' about?

828
00:41:28,567 --> 00:41:30,233
Scarzi: 'Cause I know 
 about you and Jimmy.

829
00:41:30,267 --> 00:41:33,733
Come on, Jimmy's been talkin' 
 for years about his bank,

830
00:41:33,767 --> 00:41:35,167
doin' the bank.

831
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:36,467
They want their dough!

832
00:41:36,500 --> 00:41:38,300
You know it's theirs!

833
00:41:38,333 --> 00:41:40,067
I don't know anything
about any bank.

834
00:41:40,067 --> 00:41:41,100
Come on, man.
They know!

835
00:41:41,133 --> 00:41:42,133
You know something?

836
00:41:42,167 --> 00:41:44,467
They got photographs,
they got folders,

837
00:41:44,500 --> 00:41:46,267
they got stuff on your life.

838
00:41:46,300 --> 00:41:49,200
They got a whole profile.

839
00:41:49,233 --> 00:41:50,900
A profile.

840
00:41:50,933 --> 00:41:52,633
Scarzi: They put a hood 
 over my head,

841
00:41:52,667 --> 00:41:53,700
they took me for a ride.

842
00:41:53,733 --> 00:41:56,333
I thought I was finished.
I thought I was gonzo!

843
00:41:56,367 --> 00:42:00,067
They got an ice pick.
They cut me real bad.

844
00:42:00,067 --> 00:42:02,067
(sigh)
I wasn't involved, Nick.

845
00:42:02,100 --> 00:42:07,633
Scarzi: They just call me 
 tomorrow at noon, at my place.

846
00:42:07,667 --> 00:42:11,667
I'll call you.

847
00:42:11,700 --> 00:42:13,767
- (sighs)
- (knocking)

848
00:42:16,833 --> 00:42:18,300
Captain Gerald Clemente?

849
00:42:18,333 --> 00:42:19,567
Yeah, that's right.

850
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:21,067
Hal Phillips, Federal
Bureau of Investigation.

851
00:42:21,067 --> 00:42:22,767
This is my partner, Jack Burton.

852
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:24,333
We're here in connection
with the burglary

853
00:42:24,367 --> 00:42:25,967
of the Depositor's Trust
in Medford

854
00:42:26,067 --> 00:42:27,600
over the Memorial Day weekend.

855
00:42:27,633 --> 00:42:28,967
Like to ask you a couple
of questions about it,

856
00:42:29,067 --> 00:42:30,433
if that's all right.

857
00:42:30,467 --> 00:42:32,333
Yeah, sure, sure.
Come on in, guys.

858
00:42:32,367 --> 00:42:36,600
(children giggling)

859
00:42:36,633 --> 00:42:39,600
(door squeaking)

860
00:42:41,367 --> 00:42:42,600
Can I get you guys some coffee?

861
00:42:42,633 --> 00:42:44,067
Something to drink?
Some soda?

862
00:42:44,067 --> 00:42:46,267
No, thanks.

863
00:42:46,300 --> 00:42:47,800
Captain Clemente,

864
00:42:47,833 --> 00:42:50,367
the law requires that we tell
you that you're a suspect

865
00:42:50,400 --> 00:42:52,433
in the burglary.

866
00:42:52,467 --> 00:42:53,767
On what grounds?

867
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:55,433
We're not at liberty to say.

868
00:42:55,467 --> 00:42:58,067
Oh, should I be
talking to a lawyer?

869
00:42:58,100 --> 00:42:59,700
(laughs)

870
00:42:59,733 --> 00:43:00,933
We can't advise you on that.

871
00:43:00,967 --> 00:43:04,367
That's strictly
your own decision.

872
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:06,567
I didn't have anything
to do with this, guys.

873
00:43:06,600 --> 00:43:07,667
You're not under arrest,

874
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:09,167
and no arrest is anticipated.

875
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:11,067
We'd just like to ask
you a couple questions.

876
00:43:11,067 --> 00:43:13,133
Sure, shoot.

877
00:43:13,167 --> 00:43:16,067
Can you account
for your whereabouts

878
00:43:16,067 --> 00:43:18,067
Memorial Day weekend?

879
00:43:18,100 --> 00:43:23,067
(sighs) MDC Friday night
shift into Saturday morning...

880
00:43:23,100 --> 00:43:25,400
slept back here and
worked on my boat

881
00:43:25,433 --> 00:43:27,733
down at the marina. That's it.

882
00:43:27,767 --> 00:43:32,800
We'd like it in a
little more detail.

883
00:43:32,833 --> 00:43:38,700
Okay. Well, look.

884
00:43:38,733 --> 00:43:42,533
Can I keep this between us?

885
00:43:42,567 --> 00:43:45,800
You know, off the record?

886
00:43:45,833 --> 00:43:48,200
Go ahead.

887
00:43:48,233 --> 00:43:52,400
But don't waltz us around.

888
00:43:52,433 --> 00:43:54,200
That weekend,
like most weekends,

889
00:43:54,233 --> 00:43:58,067
I spent with a friend,

890
00:43:58,067 --> 00:43:59,133
you know what I mean?

891
00:43:59,167 --> 00:44:01,333
The FBI? Maybe a grand jury?

892
00:44:01,367 --> 00:44:03,267
Gerry, what do you
expect me to say?

893
00:44:03,300 --> 00:44:04,967
I don't know the exact times

894
00:44:05,067 --> 00:44:07,600
that you were here those nights!

895
00:44:07,633 --> 00:44:14,133
How do I know you
didn't do that bank job?

896
00:44:14,167 --> 00:44:15,333
'Cause I'm
tellin' ya I didn't,

897
00:44:15,367 --> 00:44:17,800
that's why.

898
00:44:17,833 --> 00:44:19,600
Now listen.
Just tell them

899
00:44:19,633 --> 00:44:22,633
that I was here.

900
00:44:22,667 --> 00:44:24,467
And that I stayed
until the morning.

901
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:27,367
Okay?

902
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:29,067
You think I'm looking
forward to having this

903
00:44:29,100 --> 00:44:30,600
out in the open, huh?

904
00:44:30,633 --> 00:44:36,200
I had to tell the FBI the truth.

905
00:44:36,233 --> 00:44:40,333
As nasty as it is.

906
00:44:40,367 --> 00:44:42,167
Well, thanks a lot!

907
00:44:42,200 --> 00:44:44,067
Baby, come on.

908
00:44:44,067 --> 00:44:45,300
You're my legit alibi!

909
00:44:45,333 --> 00:44:49,767
Anything else
would be suspicious.

910
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:51,100
By the way,

911
00:44:51,133 --> 00:44:54,667
Mary's gonna love
hearing about this.

912
00:44:54,700 --> 00:44:57,533
Oh, now it's poor Mary, huh?

913
00:44:57,567 --> 00:44:59,733
Gerry, how's the divorce
coming along?

914
00:44:59,767 --> 00:45:03,267
Baby, this is not the time!

915
00:45:03,300 --> 00:45:06,067
It's never the right time.

916
00:45:06,067 --> 00:45:07,533
Hey, come on now.

917
00:45:07,567 --> 00:45:09,833
Come on.

918
00:45:09,867 --> 00:45:12,467
Do this for me, okay?

919
00:45:12,500 --> 00:45:13,967
Okay, baby?

920
00:45:14,067 --> 00:45:15,767
- Say yes.
- Yes.

921
00:45:15,800 --> 00:45:19,900
Give me a kiss. Big kiss.

922
00:45:19,933 --> 00:45:24,400
Big kiss.

923
00:45:24,433 --> 00:45:25,700
Want a beer?

924
00:45:25,733 --> 00:45:29,400
No.

925
00:45:29,433 --> 00:45:30,800
Confidential sources 
 believe the vault

926
00:45:30,833 --> 00:45:32,800
may have contained millions 
 of dollars in mob money,

927
00:45:32,833 --> 00:45:35,300
which would make it the largest
 bank robbery in history.

928
00:45:35,333 --> 00:45:36,633
Gerry! Get in here, quick!

929
00:45:36,667 --> 00:45:37,700
According to 
 authorized sources...

930
00:45:37,733 --> 00:45:38,900
- What's up, babe?
 - ...the immediate suspicion

931
00:45:38,933 --> 00:45:40,067
has focused on a police officer.

932
00:45:40,067 --> 00:45:41,100
Look! It's your house!

933
00:45:41,133 --> 00:45:42,767
A captain on the 
 Metropolitan Police Force

934
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:45,200
with reputed connections
to underworld figures...

935
00:45:45,233 --> 00:45:48,700
That's my house, creep!
Who the hell needs a name?

936
00:45:48,733 --> 00:45:50,933
Find out who did this
I'm gonna kill him!

937
00:45:50,967 --> 00:45:53,200
I didn't see who ran
me off the road, Dad!

938
00:45:53,233 --> 00:45:54,467
Yeah.

939
00:45:54,500 --> 00:45:55,867
They came up from behind!

940
00:45:55,900 --> 00:45:57,667
I don't know,
maybe it was an accident!

941
00:45:57,700 --> 00:46:01,067
That was no damn accident!

942
00:46:01,100 --> 00:46:04,400
Look, whoever is leaking
these lies about me

943
00:46:04,433 --> 00:46:06,967
has got the mob convinced
that I took their cash.

944
00:46:07,067 --> 00:46:09,233
Or didn't make tribute!

945
00:46:09,267 --> 00:46:10,367
Well, what's tribute?

946
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:11,967
Forget about that, okay?

947
00:46:12,067 --> 00:46:13,167
- Here, keep this on.
- Ow!

948
00:46:13,200 --> 00:46:16,567
Tight!

949
00:46:16,600 --> 00:46:18,267
- Tell me, Gerry.
- What?

950
00:46:18,300 --> 00:46:19,433
Don't give me "What?".

951
00:46:19,467 --> 00:46:20,933
Everybody in this
town knows "what"!

952
00:46:20,967 --> 00:46:22,900
- The bank!
- Mary!

953
00:46:22,933 --> 00:46:24,433
Don't lie to me, Gerry.

954
00:46:24,467 --> 00:46:27,500
Tell me!
What's it gonna take?

955
00:46:27,533 --> 00:46:30,067
What is it gonna take
to get the truth?

956
00:46:30,067 --> 00:46:31,567
One of us getting killed?

957
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:33,233
Mary, Mary, Mary, Mary.

958
00:46:33,267 --> 00:46:34,667
Come here baby, come here.

959
00:46:34,700 --> 00:46:36,267
Come here, come here.

960
00:46:36,300 --> 00:46:40,167
That's it. That's it.

961
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:42,300
I swear to God I didn't
have anything to do

962
00:46:42,333 --> 00:46:44,367
with that bank job.

963
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:45,967
I'm a cop.

964
00:46:46,067 --> 00:46:48,067
And the mob's after
my kid for no reason.

965
00:46:48,067 --> 00:46:48,967
(glass breaking)
(Mary screams)

966
00:46:49,067 --> 00:46:51,100
Get down!
Hey! Hey!

967
00:46:51,133 --> 00:46:52,067
(gun cock click)

968
00:46:52,067 --> 00:46:54,833
Come on! Hey! Hey!

969
00:46:54,867 --> 00:46:59,533
Hey! Hey!
Come on, come on.

970
00:46:59,567 --> 00:47:02,600
- Hey! Hey!
- Mary: Gerry, no!

971
00:47:02,633 --> 00:47:03,800
- Come on I'll take one of you--
- No, stop! Please!

972
00:47:03,833 --> 00:47:05,133
Get inside!

973
00:47:05,167 --> 00:47:06,900
- Get inside!
- Mary: Stop!

974
00:47:06,933 --> 00:47:08,467
Please, please!

975
00:47:12,867 --> 00:47:15,167
(sirens)
(honking)

976
00:47:17,767 --> 00:47:19,400
I wanna go
after the Feds, Jake.

977
00:47:19,433 --> 00:47:21,400
Uh-huh, that's right.

978
00:47:21,433 --> 00:47:23,067
They come to my neighborhood,

979
00:47:23,067 --> 00:47:24,133
they come to my house,

980
00:47:24,167 --> 00:47:25,633
they bother my family.

981
00:47:25,667 --> 00:47:27,733
I'm a police captain,
for crying out loud

982
00:47:27,767 --> 00:47:28,767
and they do this!

983
00:47:28,800 --> 00:47:30,467
Oh, yeah, my wife,
she can't even go out

984
00:47:30,500 --> 00:47:32,067
in the neighborhood anymore,
Jake!

985
00:47:32,100 --> 00:47:33,500
The mob tried to kill my kid!

986
00:47:33,533 --> 00:47:39,333
Yeah, and they're buying
into this setup real good.

987
00:47:39,367 --> 00:47:41,067
What can I do to help, Gerry?

988
00:47:41,067 --> 00:47:42,833
Anything. Name it!

989
00:47:42,867 --> 00:47:47,267
(sighs) Well, naturally,
I came to you first,

990
00:47:47,300 --> 00:47:50,167
to see if I could
straighten things out.

991
00:47:50,200 --> 00:47:52,433
Jake, I swear to God,

992
00:47:52,467 --> 00:47:54,500
I'm completely innocent
on this thing.

993
00:47:54,533 --> 00:47:56,067
You gotta help me.

994
00:47:56,100 --> 00:47:58,400
Okay.

995
00:47:58,433 --> 00:48:01,200
Look, you got 40 days
vacation coming.

996
00:48:01,233 --> 00:48:03,300
I want you to take it,
for your sake.

997
00:48:03,333 --> 00:48:05,100
You need the break.

998
00:48:05,133 --> 00:48:09,167
As far as the department goes,

999
00:48:09,200 --> 00:48:14,067
I think it better if the Feds
just think I'm standin' still.

1000
00:48:14,067 --> 00:48:15,967
Don't stand still.
Get into it.

1001
00:48:16,067 --> 00:48:17,800
Go after them for harassment.

1002
00:48:17,833 --> 00:48:20,167
There's nothin' to
go after them with!

1003
00:48:20,200 --> 00:48:23,067
You need proof
to press harassment,

1004
00:48:23,100 --> 00:48:26,100
not just leak some rumors!

1005
00:48:26,133 --> 00:48:29,633
Take a 40 day fast, Gerry.

1006
00:48:29,667 --> 00:48:31,667
It's for the best!

1007
00:48:31,700 --> 00:48:34,900
Look, I'm on your side here.

1008
00:48:34,933 --> 00:48:37,433
Right now, it looks
like I'm the only one.

1009
00:48:37,467 --> 00:48:38,467
Trust me!

1010
00:48:47,067 --> 00:48:49,267
(spraying)

1011
00:49:03,667 --> 00:49:07,700
Oh. Mastermind
of Depositor's Trust

1012
00:49:07,733 --> 00:49:09,567
finally pays me a visit.

1013
00:49:09,600 --> 00:49:13,200
I didn't mastermind
anything, Mr. Ferrara.

1014
00:49:13,233 --> 00:49:16,533
Mr. Ferrara.

1015
00:49:16,567 --> 00:49:19,400
Don't go too far with the
dog and pony show, Gerry.

1016
00:49:19,433 --> 00:49:20,700
Doesn't suit you.

1017
00:49:20,733 --> 00:49:22,833
I tell you it wasn't my idea.

1018
00:49:22,867 --> 00:49:24,600
That's what you'd
like everybody to think,

1019
00:49:24,633 --> 00:49:25,733
even your partners.

1020
00:49:25,767 --> 00:49:27,067
I work like that.

1021
00:49:27,067 --> 00:49:28,767
It's a good thing to
keep in the background,

1022
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:29,867
still pull the strings.

1023
00:49:29,900 --> 00:49:31,100
That's a smart thing.

1024
00:49:31,133 --> 00:49:32,700
What's not so smart,

1025
00:49:32,733 --> 00:49:35,633
is you not paying me tribute.

1026
00:49:35,667 --> 00:49:36,933
Excuse me?

1027
00:49:36,967 --> 00:49:38,233
Not for nothin',

1028
00:49:38,267 --> 00:49:41,100
but my alarm man
paid off from Florida.

1029
00:49:41,133 --> 00:49:43,067
I haven't seen a dime, Gerry.

1030
00:49:43,100 --> 00:49:46,933
Why?

1031
00:49:46,967 --> 00:49:50,300
I don't know, I...

1032
00:49:50,333 --> 00:49:52,700
I have to get in touch
with my man.

1033
00:49:52,733 --> 00:49:54,800
I'm not in contact with him.

1034
00:49:54,833 --> 00:49:56,667
That's not so smart.

1035
00:49:56,700 --> 00:49:58,567
Should keep a tighter
rein on your people.

1036
00:49:58,600 --> 00:50:00,200
Somebody could get hurt.

1037
00:50:00,233 --> 00:50:03,800
I'm givin' it to you straight.

1038
00:50:03,833 --> 00:50:05,267
I know what's bothering you.

1039
00:50:05,300 --> 00:50:07,067
You got a lot more out of
the bank than you expected

1040
00:50:07,100 --> 00:50:08,633
and had your boys worried.

1041
00:50:08,667 --> 00:50:10,967
You've been thinkin' maybe
some of it belonged to me.

1042
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:13,967
Did cross my mind, yes.
(clears throat)

1043
00:50:14,000 --> 00:50:15,433
Relax.
It was a clean score.

1044
00:50:15,467 --> 00:50:17,267
None of it was mine.

1045
00:50:17,300 --> 00:50:18,500
Just want my cut,

1046
00:50:18,533 --> 00:50:20,200
you'll have nothing
to worry about.

1047
00:50:20,233 --> 00:50:22,167
What about Nick Scarzi, huh?

1048
00:50:22,200 --> 00:50:24,133
He tells me that you're
threatening to put an ice pick

1049
00:50:24,167 --> 00:50:26,000
in his head
unless I pay him off.

1050
00:50:26,033 --> 00:50:27,133
Scarzi's nothing.

1051
00:50:27,167 --> 00:50:28,867
My boys tell me the only
ones giving him a hard time

1052
00:50:28,900 --> 00:50:32,533
are the Feds.

1053
00:50:32,567 --> 00:50:34,600
Scarzi's disappeared?

1054
00:50:34,633 --> 00:50:36,300
I thought he was supposed
to be under your wing?

1055
00:50:36,333 --> 00:50:38,000
We never did a deal with him.

1056
00:50:38,033 --> 00:50:39,833
Scarzi's a loose cannon.

1057
00:50:39,867 --> 00:50:41,000
If he's squeezing Clemente,

1058
00:50:41,033 --> 00:50:43,967
he's doin' it
on his own. Dammit.

1059
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:45,467
Listen.
(phone ringing)

1060
00:50:45,500 --> 00:50:47,600
I'm as frustrated by this
case as you are, Phillips.

1061
00:50:47,633 --> 00:50:49,167
Believe me. Let me clue you.

1062
00:50:49,200 --> 00:50:51,233
Washington's not gonna
wanna be at the table

1063
00:50:51,267 --> 00:50:53,067
if the grand jury
comes up craps.

1064
00:50:53,100 --> 00:50:54,400
Once this case goes south,

1065
00:50:54,433 --> 00:50:56,500
you'll be packing up
this show in a week!

1066
00:50:56,533 --> 00:50:58,600
Tell me something
I don't know.

1067
00:50:58,633 --> 00:51:00,167
Look, I don't
know about you guys,

1068
00:51:00,200 --> 00:51:01,633
But I've been takin'
some serious heat.

1069
00:51:01,667 --> 00:51:02,867
I'm still on parole.

1070
00:51:02,900 --> 00:51:04,200
Feds are watching every move.

1071
00:51:04,233 --> 00:51:05,300
The way things are now,

1072
00:51:05,333 --> 00:51:08,567
I can't even get to the jewels!

1073
00:51:08,600 --> 00:51:10,067
Did you pay
tribute to Ferrara?

1074
00:51:10,100 --> 00:51:11,333
Oh, yeah, a lot of laughs.

1075
00:51:11,367 --> 00:51:13,833
It's suicide to try to
move anything right now.

1076
00:51:13,867 --> 00:51:15,500
It's just too hot!

1077
00:51:15,533 --> 00:51:16,967
Yeah?

1078
00:51:17,067 --> 00:51:18,333
Well it's gonna get a
hell of a lot hotter

1079
00:51:18,367 --> 00:51:21,867
if we don't see ours soon.

1080
00:51:21,900 --> 00:51:22,933
All it takes, Frank,

1081
00:51:22,967 --> 00:51:24,133
is just one little thing,

1082
00:51:24,167 --> 00:51:25,567
a ring, a watch, to
fall in the wrong hands.

1083
00:51:25,600 --> 00:51:28,700
And bang!
We're nailed.

1084
00:51:28,733 --> 00:51:32,067
Look, you can't be
too careful moving it.

1085
00:51:32,067 --> 00:51:34,733
Now look, just as soon as
the Feds are off my back,

1086
00:51:34,767 --> 00:51:37,733
I'll get down to some business.
I promise.

1087
00:51:37,767 --> 00:51:40,600
You promise, huh?

1088
00:51:40,633 --> 00:51:43,933
Benny, I got somethin'
I wanna show you.

1089
00:51:49,133 --> 00:51:52,100
(sniffing)

1090
00:51:59,667 --> 00:52:04,067
This is an interesting
piece, isn't it?

1091
00:52:04,067 --> 00:52:06,467
It's just somethin' I picked up.

1092
00:52:06,500 --> 00:52:08,067
(clicking)

1093
00:52:08,100 --> 00:52:10,167
What do you think, Benny?

1094
00:52:10,200 --> 00:52:11,433
Come on Gerry, come on!

1095
00:52:11,467 --> 00:52:13,467
I don't deserve this!

1096
00:52:18,900 --> 00:52:20,400
I think he gets the point,
Frankie.

1097
00:52:26,267 --> 00:52:27,533
(snap)

1098
00:52:27,567 --> 00:52:30,067
That's it?

1099
00:52:30,067 --> 00:52:33,367
That's all the FBI has
on the good Captain?

1100
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:35,967
It's not much.

1101
00:52:36,067 --> 00:52:39,267
What have you got on him?

1102
00:52:39,300 --> 00:52:44,467
Departmental misconduct
with an on duty affair.

1103
00:52:44,500 --> 00:52:46,600
That's it.

1104
00:52:46,633 --> 00:52:47,833
Jake: I'm looking for
bigger things.

1105
00:52:47,867 --> 00:52:49,533
Payoffs, kickbacks, bribery.

1106
00:52:49,567 --> 00:52:52,067
But no other cops
have come forward yet

1107
00:52:52,100 --> 00:52:55,133
to corroborate the
kind of stuff I need.

1108
00:52:55,167 --> 00:52:56,833
What you need for what, Jake?

1109
00:52:56,867 --> 00:52:58,833
To bust Clemente
down and take his bars.

1110
00:52:58,867 --> 00:53:00,167
That's the only way
I'm gonna put him

1111
00:53:00,200 --> 00:53:01,733
and the rest of his gang in jail

1112
00:53:01,767 --> 00:53:03,800
for the Depositor's Trust.

1113
00:53:03,833 --> 00:53:05,400
How does that follow?

1114
00:53:05,433 --> 00:53:09,267
I've got Gerry thinking I'm
the only one he can trust.

1115
00:53:09,300 --> 00:53:11,400
On that score, I wanna
keep him spinning so fast

1116
00:53:11,433 --> 00:53:14,100
he doesn't know where
I'm coming from.

1117
00:53:14,133 --> 00:53:15,267
Here's the tactic.

1118
00:53:15,300 --> 00:53:17,833
I sucker him in close, get some
cops to break omertà.

1119
00:53:17,867 --> 00:53:21,800
then put pressure on
Gerry until he cracks.

1120
00:53:21,833 --> 00:53:24,267
According to the Feds, there
had to be four to five guys

1121
00:53:24,300 --> 00:53:27,467
including Clemente,
inside the bank.

1122
00:53:27,500 --> 00:53:30,067
Smart guys,
and moreover, tight.

1123
00:53:30,100 --> 00:53:32,433
Gerry's the pin, the glue
that holds them together.

1124
00:53:32,467 --> 00:53:34,767
I wanna keep the heat on him.

1125
00:53:34,800 --> 00:53:37,067
I bust him down,
I loosen the glue,

1126
00:53:37,067 --> 00:53:40,667
I loosen the glue,
I get the gang.

1127
00:53:48,800 --> 00:53:51,067
Gerry, I hate to
keep harping on this,

1128
00:53:51,067 --> 00:53:53,100
but Commissioner Kirkland
still wants you in

1129
00:53:53,133 --> 00:53:55,533
for a polygraph on
the Depositor's Trust.

1130
00:53:55,567 --> 00:53:56,733
Kirkland? That suit?

1131
00:53:56,767 --> 00:53:58,333
You're on the line, you should
be able to hold him off.

1132
00:53:58,367 --> 00:54:02,067
Gerry, the man's all over me!

1133
00:54:02,067 --> 00:54:07,333
All right Jake... I'll do it.

1134
00:54:07,367 --> 00:54:09,867
But it's a no-win deal.
I don't trust those things.

1135
00:54:09,900 --> 00:54:11,367
I'm going in there
involuntarily,

1136
00:54:11,400 --> 00:54:15,200
so they can't
hold it against me.

1137
00:54:15,233 --> 00:54:17,233
You have to sign this.

1138
00:54:17,267 --> 00:54:19,567
You can get an attorney,
if you want one.

1139
00:54:19,600 --> 00:54:22,567
Attorney?
You sound like the Feds!

1140
00:54:22,600 --> 00:54:26,933
Gimme a break!
Give me a break.

1141
00:54:26,967 --> 00:54:28,067
You want an attorney?

1142
00:54:28,067 --> 00:54:29,167
You can have one.
That's all.

1143
00:54:29,200 --> 00:54:32,333
I'm just trying
to help you out!

1144
00:54:32,367 --> 00:54:38,567
(police sirens in the distance)

1145
00:54:38,600 --> 00:54:39,667
This is on for tomorrow!

1146
00:54:39,700 --> 00:54:41,367
How am I gonna get an attorney?

1147
00:54:41,400 --> 00:54:43,567
What's that gonna look like?

1148
00:54:43,600 --> 00:54:45,433
This is nuts.

1149
00:54:45,467 --> 00:54:46,767
If they've got enough evidence,

1150
00:54:46,800 --> 00:54:48,400
why not the hell
just indict me?

1151
00:54:48,433 --> 00:54:49,767
Answer me that, huh?

1152
00:54:49,800 --> 00:54:51,100
I can't.

1153
00:54:51,133 --> 00:54:53,667
Look, look, look!

1154
00:54:53,700 --> 00:54:55,800
Take the test.

1155
00:54:55,833 --> 00:54:57,700
It'll clear the air!

1156
00:54:57,733 --> 00:54:59,300
What's the problem?

1157
00:54:59,333 --> 00:55:00,800
The problem is,

1158
00:55:00,833 --> 00:55:04,067
that I expected a lot more
support from the department.

1159
00:55:04,100 --> 00:55:07,267
The problem, Jake,

1160
00:55:07,300 --> 00:55:11,400
is that I expected a
lot more from you, okay?

1161
00:55:11,433 --> 00:55:17,800
I do what I can, Gerry.

1162
00:55:17,833 --> 00:55:19,333
Here.

1163
00:55:19,367 --> 00:55:22,333
(heavy breathing)

1164
00:55:34,333 --> 00:55:36,767
Gerry, I'm telling you that
somebody is watching my house!

1165
00:55:36,800 --> 00:55:38,867
Will you stop it Kelly,
this is ridiculous.

1166
00:55:38,900 --> 00:55:40,267
I'm a cop, this is
what I do for a living.

1167
00:55:40,300 --> 00:55:41,400
I would know all this.

1168
00:55:41,433 --> 00:55:44,833
Here, see? Nothin'.

1169
00:55:44,867 --> 00:55:47,333
- Gerry, I'm scared!
- Gerry: No need.

1170
00:55:47,367 --> 00:55:50,100
Gerry, I'm not lying!
Why would I lie?

1171
00:55:50,133 --> 00:55:53,933
Maybe because
you miss me, baby.

1172
00:55:53,967 --> 00:55:55,767
Did you ever think of that?

1173
00:55:55,800 --> 00:55:57,533
- (Kelly sighs)
- There's my baby.

1174
00:55:57,567 --> 00:56:00,967
Well, maybe just a little.

1175
00:56:01,067 --> 00:56:04,300
That's my girl.

1176
00:56:04,333 --> 00:56:05,600
That's my baby.

1177
00:56:05,633 --> 00:56:08,100
You know, maybe I haven't
seen as much of you

1178
00:56:08,133 --> 00:56:10,800
as I've wanted to
since this leave.

1179
00:56:10,833 --> 00:56:12,967
Well, that's easily remedied.

1180
00:56:13,067 --> 00:56:14,500
Oh, baby! Oh!

1181
00:56:24,867 --> 00:56:28,500
Gerry! Look!

1182
00:56:28,533 --> 00:56:32,200
Cops!

1183
00:56:32,233 --> 00:56:35,133
Hey! Hey, come here!

1184
00:56:35,167 --> 00:56:36,400
(squealing tires)

1185
00:56:36,433 --> 00:56:37,700
Come on! Come here!

1186
00:56:37,733 --> 00:56:39,533
Come here, ya dirt bag!

1187
00:56:39,567 --> 00:56:41,067
(dog barking in the distance)

1188
00:56:41,100 --> 00:56:44,800
(car door open)
(engine revving)

1189
00:56:44,833 --> 00:56:50,233
(tires screeching)

1190
00:57:02,067 --> 00:57:05,167
Come on, come on!

1191
00:57:05,200 --> 00:57:07,067
Come on!

1192
00:57:07,067 --> 00:57:11,067
That's it!

1193
00:57:11,067 --> 00:57:12,500
(tires screeching)

1194
00:57:12,533 --> 00:57:13,800
(honking)

1195
00:57:16,300 --> 00:57:18,300
(tires screeching)

1196
00:57:28,700 --> 00:57:29,800
Here we go!

1197
00:57:33,900 --> 00:57:35,433
(tires screeching)

1198
00:57:37,100 --> 00:57:38,900
Dammit! I'm off duty, man!

1199
00:57:38,933 --> 00:57:41,100
I don't need you guys
comin' around here!

1200
00:57:41,133 --> 00:57:42,833
- Hey! What's the problem?
- Gerry: What's the problem?

1201
00:57:42,867 --> 00:57:43,700
You know what the problem is!

1202
00:57:43,733 --> 00:57:45,300
I was just
investigating an accident!

1203
00:57:45,333 --> 00:57:47,067
Well, stay off my back
or I'll give you something

1204
00:57:47,067 --> 00:57:51,967
to investigate!

1205
00:57:52,067 --> 00:57:52,800
Get outta here.

1206
00:57:52,833 --> 00:57:55,400
- Okay.
- Get the hell outta here!

1207
00:57:58,533 --> 00:58:00,067
(engine revving)

1208
00:58:00,100 --> 00:58:01,600
(tires screeching)

1209
00:58:04,400 --> 00:58:06,100
You got nothin' on me!

1210
00:58:06,133 --> 00:58:07,667
Nothin'!

1211
00:58:29,967 --> 00:58:31,167
What do you got?

1212
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:32,367
You know Bobby Kellogg?

1213
00:58:32,400 --> 00:58:33,767
Sure, I pensioned
him out of narcotics

1214
00:58:33,800 --> 00:58:35,133
a couple of months ago. Why?

1215
00:58:35,167 --> 00:58:36,633
I'm on to something hot.

1216
00:58:36,667 --> 00:58:38,567
Rumor is Gerry tried to
bribe him off a drug bust

1217
00:58:38,600 --> 00:58:40,067
just before that.

1218
00:58:40,067 --> 00:58:41,400
Kellogg didn't go for it.

1219
00:58:41,433 --> 00:58:43,067
Jake: Rumor according
to who?

1220
00:58:43,100 --> 00:58:44,600
A narcotics cop.

1221
00:58:44,633 --> 00:58:46,167
No way he'll come forward.

1222
00:58:46,200 --> 00:58:50,633
I got Kellogg tracked,
he doesn't wanna come in.

1223
00:58:50,667 --> 00:58:51,900
He's up and down, Jake.

1224
00:58:51,933 --> 00:58:53,767
I don't know what kinda
witness he's gonna make.

1225
00:58:53,800 --> 00:58:55,400
Our only witness.

1226
00:58:55,433 --> 00:58:57,900
He won't talk to
me about anything.

1227
00:58:57,933 --> 00:58:59,733
I danced around what
we wanted to know,

1228
00:58:59,767 --> 00:59:01,200
he wouldn't bite.

1229
00:59:01,233 --> 00:59:03,067
Said he'd only talk to you.

1230
00:59:03,067 --> 00:59:05,200
In secret, and off the record.

1231
00:59:05,233 --> 00:59:08,333
Set it up.
Any place, anywhere.

1232
00:59:08,367 --> 00:59:10,200
You got the word,
Gerry could get the word.

1233
00:59:10,233 --> 00:59:11,467
I wanna move on this now.

1234
00:59:11,500 --> 00:59:12,700
Move how?

1235
00:59:12,733 --> 00:59:14,567
Whatever Kellogg gives us,

1236
00:59:14,600 --> 00:59:17,067
I'll slip into the polygraph.

1237
00:59:17,067 --> 00:59:19,867
That ought to get Gerry hoppin'.

1238
00:59:19,900 --> 00:59:20,933
Gerry: That wasn't
a lie detector test,

1239
00:59:20,967 --> 00:59:22,067
that was an inquisition!

1240
00:59:22,067 --> 00:59:23,300
Something's wrong here, Jake!

1241
00:59:23,333 --> 00:59:24,533
What do you mean?

1242
00:59:24,567 --> 00:59:25,767
Gerry: I mean that wasn't the
regular polygraph guy.

1243
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:27,067
That was a fed, I could feel it,

1244
00:59:27,067 --> 00:59:28,500
I could hear it the
way he was talking.

1245
00:59:28,533 --> 00:59:30,167
I mean it's probably all
taped and that's illegal.

1246
00:59:30,200 --> 00:59:31,433
Jake: It would be.

1247
00:59:31,467 --> 00:59:32,633
Gerry: Yeah. Yeah.
Well, listen,

1248
00:59:32,667 --> 00:59:34,433
I don't like this whole thing.
You should be behind me,

1249
00:59:34,467 --> 00:59:35,900
instead of draggin'
me over here.

1250
00:59:35,933 --> 00:59:37,333
I am behind you,
but you gotta remember,

1251
00:59:37,367 --> 00:59:40,200
Commissioner Kirkland's
behind me with a cattle prod.

1252
00:59:40,233 --> 00:59:42,133
Cops are under investigation
and he wants the truth!

1253
00:59:42,167 --> 00:59:43,533
The truth?

1254
00:59:43,567 --> 00:59:45,400
The truth is that I'm
being set up with a bogus

1255
00:59:45,433 --> 00:59:46,500
lie detector test.

1256
00:59:46,533 --> 00:59:48,633
The truth is that I'm being
spied on in my own house

1257
00:59:48,667 --> 00:59:49,800
at four o'clock in the morning,

1258
00:59:49,833 --> 00:59:51,133
from guys from my
own department.

1259
00:59:51,167 --> 00:59:52,700
Your department, Jake.

1260
00:59:52,733 --> 00:59:54,533
What do you mean by that?

1261
00:59:54,567 --> 00:59:57,167
(sighs) I mean, whose
side are you on, huh?

1262
00:59:57,200 --> 00:59:58,733
I'm on your side, Gerry,

1263
00:59:58,767 --> 01:00:00,400
but I've got pressure on me.

1264
01:00:00,433 --> 01:00:02,100
Lots of it.

1265
01:00:02,133 --> 01:00:06,467
I'll bet.
Let's get outta here.

1266
01:00:06,500 --> 01:00:08,167
(tires squealing)

1267
01:00:42,367 --> 01:00:44,133
Bobby Kellogg,
how ya doin'?

1268
01:00:44,167 --> 01:00:45,467
Cut to the chase, Quinn,

1269
01:00:45,500 --> 01:00:46,667
what do you want?

1270
01:00:46,700 --> 01:00:49,300
I want you to
give me Clemente.

1271
01:00:49,333 --> 01:00:50,333
Clemente's not mine to give.

1272
01:00:50,367 --> 01:00:51,567
What do I know?

1273
01:00:51,600 --> 01:00:53,333
You know about the
Wellington Circle bust.

1274
01:00:53,367 --> 01:00:54,933
Clemente tried to
bribe you, didn't he?

1275
01:00:54,967 --> 01:00:56,167
He offered you money,
you refused.

1276
01:00:56,200 --> 01:00:59,067
Dealers went down.
Clemente told Scarzi--

1277
01:00:59,100 --> 01:01:01,600
Well you know so damn much,
what do you need me for?

1278
01:01:01,633 --> 01:01:03,300
I wanna bring
him up on charges.

1279
01:01:03,333 --> 01:01:05,467
I wanna take away his bars.

1280
01:01:05,500 --> 01:01:07,600
And I need your
testimony to do that.

1281
01:01:07,633 --> 01:01:10,667
Without you,
I've got nothing on him.

1282
01:01:10,700 --> 01:01:13,867
Then you got nothin'.

1283
01:01:13,900 --> 01:01:15,567
Gerry's dirty, Bobby.

1284
01:01:15,600 --> 01:01:17,233
He stinks to hell.

1285
01:01:17,267 --> 01:01:19,533
And that makes guys
like you and me stink too.

1286
01:01:19,567 --> 01:01:20,900
Good cops.

1287
01:01:20,933 --> 01:01:25,633
Even good cops
don't rat on cops, man.

1288
01:01:25,667 --> 01:01:27,667
He shouldn't be
on the streets.

1289
01:01:27,700 --> 01:01:29,200
He shouldn't be
wearing a badge.

1290
01:01:29,233 --> 01:01:30,567
It's not right,
you know it's not right!

1291
01:01:30,600 --> 01:01:31,600
Right?

1292
01:01:31,633 --> 01:01:32,667
What's right anymore, man?

1293
01:01:32,700 --> 01:01:33,767
He's a cop!

1294
01:01:33,800 --> 01:01:35,067
No he's not.

1295
01:01:35,100 --> 01:01:36,200
Nothing like you were.

1296
01:01:36,233 --> 01:01:37,800
He's nothing like you ever were.

1297
01:01:37,833 --> 01:01:39,633
Help me bring him down.

1298
01:01:39,667 --> 01:01:41,433
Let's bring him down together.

1299
01:01:41,467 --> 01:01:44,433
I need you!
If you don't do this--

1300
01:01:44,467 --> 01:01:46,367
(squealing tires)

1301
01:01:55,267 --> 01:01:56,333
Bobby?

1302
01:02:02,300 --> 01:02:05,633
Gerry: One year down,
four to go.

1303
01:02:05,667 --> 01:02:07,067
You know something', Gerry?

1304
01:02:07,067 --> 01:02:10,733
Between your boat
and this cabin

1305
01:02:10,767 --> 01:02:12,067
you're leasing up here,

1306
01:02:12,067 --> 01:02:13,900
it's good to see you
cut loose a little man.

1307
01:02:13,933 --> 01:02:15,500
You got a little uptight,
you know?

1308
01:02:15,533 --> 01:02:17,100
Move your foot, pal.

1309
01:02:17,133 --> 01:02:20,867
Well, if push comes
to shove there stretch,

1310
01:02:20,900 --> 01:02:23,100
I could trace all of this legit.

1311
01:02:23,133 --> 01:02:24,733
